Now Margaret Thatcher has been named the owner of one of the most influential hairstyles ever created - all thanks to her trademark coiffed blonde locks.

Asked to nominate the most iconic hairstyles of all times, a poll of 2,000 British women found that Mrs Thatcher's look remains popular and even beat the long, flowing locks of the Duchess of Cambridge.

