Most popular of all though, was Jennifer Aniston's iconic 'Rachel' haircut, a look that was widely copied in the late 90s and early noughties following the transatlantic success of Friends.

Second place in the poll was taken by Marilyn Monroe's platinum blonde bob, while late singer Amy Winehouse and her trademark beehive came third.

In fourth place was Princess Diana whose short blonde crop came well ahead of her daughter-in-law's long locks which could only manage 10th spot.

60s designer Mary Quant, famous for her short graphic bob, came fifth while sixth place went to eccentric 80s singer Grace Jones.

